---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import Section from "../../components/Section.astro";
import Card from "../../components/Card.astro";

const title = "Deck Guides for One Piece Card Game";
const description = "Leader-focused One Piece Card Game deck guides with game plans, mulligans, upgrade paths, and matchup tips.";
---

<MainLayout title={title} description={description}>
	<section class="hero">
		<div class="container">
			<span class="hero-badge">Deck Guides</span>
			<h1>Deck Guides for One Piece Card Game</h1>
			<p>
				Build better lists and pilot them with purpose. These deck guides break down leader identities,
				core packages, and the key turns that define each archetype. Whether you are pushing for a top
				cut finish or learning a new leader, the goal is the same: simplify the plan so your decisions are
				clear and repeatable.
			</p>
			<p>
				Each guide focuses on three pillars. First, your opening plan: mulligan priorities, early tempo lines,
				and when to protect life versus race. Second, your mid-game: resource loops, attack sequencing, and
				how to pivot based on opposing leaders. Third, your upgrade path: the most impactful changes as your
				collection grows. You can cross-reference matchup notes in the <a href="/matchups">Matchups</a>
				section and stay aware of format shifts in <a href="/meta-analysis">Meta Analysis</a>. If you are still
				learning fundamentals, the <a href="/beginner-guides">Beginner Guides</a> will get you up to speed fast.
			</p>
			<p>
				Guides are structured to be quick to scan on mobile while still offering depth. Expect realistic
				list snapshots, tech options for common threats, and explanation of why each card matters. You can
				bookmark favorite leaders and return as new sets drop or the <a href="/banlist">Banlist</a> changes.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<Section
		title="Featured Guides"
		description="Popular leaders with clear game plans and matchup angles."
		linkHref="/deck-guides"
		linkLabel="All guides"
	>
		<Card
			eyebrow="Tempo"
			title="Red Zoro"
			description="Turn-by-turn pressure, clean curve choices, and how to keep damage flowing."
			href="/deck-guides"
		/>
		<Card
			eyebrow="Control"
			title="Blue Doflamingo"
			description="Stabilize, loop value, and set up a safe finishing sequence."
			href="/deck-guides"
		/>
		<Card
			eyebrow="Midrange"
			title="Green Uta"
			description="Balanced lines with flexible answers to the most common threats."
			href="/deck-guides"
		/>
		<Card
			eyebrow="Ramp"
			title="Purple Kaido"
			description="Explosive DON!! turns, board sweeps, and when to shift to lethal."
			href="/deck-guides"
		/>
	</Section>
</MainLayout>
